    "PH-digraphs": {
      "iCanStatement": "I can read words with sh, ch, th and ck.",
      "explanation": "Sometimes two letters team up to make ONE sound. s+h say /sh/ (ship), c+h say /ch/ (chip), t+h say /th/ (thin). At the end of a short word, c+k say /k/ (duck). Keep the two letters together as one sound.",
      "workedExamples": [
